New era starts now. I can’t believe I’m typing these words…my new album ‘Weird Faith’ is coming February 9th, 2024 on @antirecords. “Same Risk,” the first single, is out now with an accompanying video directed by myself and the lovely @elizabetholms. 

This record is about the beginning. The unwilling flailing and ultimate trust fall into love. It’s about saying every feeling out loud the second I felt it for better or worse because I can’t help it. This album exists between the time you say “I Love You” and the moment they say it back… or don’t.

"Don’t Do Me Good" is about that person that we keep coming back to, over and over again. It's about waking up every day and continuing to make the choice to love a person unconditionally without boundaries while it’s simultaneously getting harder and harder to ignore that nothing is getting better. It’s stubborn, it’s defiant, it's hopeful, and it's aggressively optimistic. I wanted this song to feel like calling your friend in that moment of needing to commiserate with someone…to talk through an experience you’re having and say it out loud to make sure it’s real. To chronicle your experience with someone in real time and to have that person say “yeah man, I’ve so been there” and share the experience with you. This song would have been so awfully lonely without that spirit in there and I’m just beyond grateful to hear Kacey’s voice on this with mine. We’ve talked a lot of life up and down and this song feels like an extension of that connection and I’m proud of that:). (call your friends!!) thank u @spaceykacey 🥲 x 

“Don't Do Me Good” featuring Kacey Musgraves. Out Now.

Y’all….“Don’t Do Me Good” is about wanting to believe that love is the only thing that matters. Constantly choosing to believe in the future of what could be, instead what is. It’s about being so good at getting through the hard parts that you don’t know love being… easy. It’s about being a bit of a masochist and being so in love with the hard work of loving a person that you don’t know how to walk away from them. 

I wrote it with the incredible @amywadge 

Really I can’t thank you enough for all the love and for listening and sharing. It means the actual world.
